{
  "stem": "22944.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's how you can call, I don't know, ultra orthodox or very, very orthodox.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I can't put to the degree of orthodox in our family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't recollect.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our family was scattered quite a bit in different parts of Slovakia, and Hungary, as well.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] one part of the family-- I think, my father maybe working, or my uncle was working with my father.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I can't tell you exactly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We used to see them from time to time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I do remember on Saturdays, afternoon teas.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother used to invite some friends or member of my family, but I reckon they might have been just friends.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't have very strong childhood memories of meeting many member of my family from my father's side.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On my mother's side, I seen-- we saw them a bit more, but then, they did not have children, except one of my auntie had a boy-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Jeremiah [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I do not really-- and then, later I had another cousin from that side of the family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But my father's side, we had been a very large family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So presumably, it was difficult to organize family gathering, because our apartment was lovely where we lived, and I think it's three bedrooms, but I doubt that we could put up another six or 10 extra people.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did not know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, I didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think they passed away before I was born.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandfather-- well, I think he was in the grocery business.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he had 13 children.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think 12 survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they lived, I think, in Piestany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a scholar, a very well-learned man.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
